---
description: Backend Laravel development rules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Laravel Standards

- Use Laravel 11 conventions whenever appropriate.
- Use strict typing.
- Use typed properties and return types.
- Prefer readonly dependencies when possible.

# Controllers

- Controllers must remain thin.
- Controllers should orchestrate actions only.
- Never place business logic in controllers.

# Validation

- Use Form Requests for validation.
- Never validate directly inside controllers.
- Keep validation explicit and readable.

# Services

- Business rules belong in service classes or actions.
- Services should have single responsibility.
- Avoid massive service classes.

# Database

- Use transactions for critical operations.
- Prevent race conditions in bidding operations.
- Use pessimistic locking when necessary.
- Avoid N+1 queries.
- Use eager loading intentionally.

# API Design

- Use API Resources for responses.
- Maintain consistent JSON structure.
- Use proper HTTP status codes.
- Never expose internal implementation details.

# Authentication & Authorization

- Use Laravel Sanctum.
- Use policies and gates for authorization.
- Never trust frontend authorization checks.

# Realtime

- WebSocket events must be minimal and efficient.
- Avoid broadcasting unnecessary data.
- Realtime updates must remain idempotent.

# Performance

- Cache expensive queries.
- Use queues for heavy tasks.
- Avoid blocking operations.

# Testing

- Create feature tests for critical flows.
- Create unit tests for business rules.
- Test transactional consistency.